<P><HI>ARCANA MOOREANA;</HI> OR, A Succinct and Lucid DISCOURSE, OF THE <HI>Origine, E&s;&s;ence, Scituation Symp|toms, Cau&s;es</HI> and <HI>Cure</HI> OF THE CHOLICK, In all its various Denominations, different Kinds, Degrees, and Complications.</P>
<P>Done by Mr. <HI>John Moore,</HI> Apothecary, at the <HI>Pe&s;tle</HI> and <HI>Mortar,</HI> in <HI>Abchurch-Lane,</HI> near <HI><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">umbard-&s;treet.</HI></P>
<Q><HI>Natura legibus e&s;&s;e Medicinae Leges con&s;entaneas, Medicus Remedia con<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="1 letter">ert, non &s;olum naturae Mini&s;ter, Sed interdum ut Opifex primarius.</HI></Q>
<P><HI>LONDON:</HI> Printed for the A<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="KEYERS" EXTENT="2 letters">hor. 1713.</P>
